description: BMO US Put Write ETF Hedged to CAD ETF has been designed to deliver an alternative income exposure by writing put options on an underlying portfolio of U.S. large cap equities. The ETF writes short-dated out-of-the-money put options by analyzing the available option premiums, while investing the portfolio in cash equivalents. The ETF may be subject to a loss if the stock prices decline significantly over the option period. The U.S. currency exposure is hedged back to Canadian dollars. In addition, as ZPH is a fund of fund, the management fees charged are reduced by those accrued in the underlying funds.
name: BMO US Put Write Hedged to CAD ETF
